The foregoing and other objects will become more readily apparent by referring to the following detailed description and the appended drawings in which:


FIG. 1 illustrates a general block diagram of the inventive method;


FIG. 2a illustrates a digitized audio signal having audio samples;


FIG. 2b illustrates a frequency domain representation of the audio samples in FIG. 2a, the frequency domain representation having 576 successive frequency lines as in ISO/IEC 13818-3 (MPEG2 layer 3);


FIG. 2c illustrates the subdivision of the frequency domain representation into 22 scale factor bands (sfb0 to sfb21) as in ISO/IEC 13818-3 (MPEG2 layer 3);


FIG. 2d illustrates the four regions (region 0 to 3) as in ISO/IEC 13818-3, region 3 being the highest region;


FIG. 2e illustrates the four regions as in FIG. 2d with zero valued scale factors in the highest region in accordance with the present invention; and


FIG. 2f illustrates the coded frequency lines for the 0th to 2nd regions for which bits are required for coding the scale factors themselves, and for the 3rd region for which no bits are required for the scale factors.
